HEADWORD: Imbrication
<hw>Im`bri*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>imbrication</ets>.]</ety> <def>An overlapping of the edges, like
that of tiles or shingles; hence, intricacy of structure; also, a
pattern or decoration representing such a structure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imbricative</ent>⟦br⟧
